It's not like we didn't want to tell you.

260
00:21:55,397 --> 00:21:57,691
Mm. So considerate.

261
00:21:58,984 --> 00:22:01,862
Oh, then what about the ten million won
that you borrowed from my mom?

262
00:22:01,945 --> 00:22:04,281
You acted like that never happened
when they divorced.

263
00:22:04,364 --> 00:22:06,450
I wonder if that's also you
being considerate.

264
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:09,161
Will you give me an answer today?

265
00:22:09,244 --> 00:22:11,788
You could always give me
the money instead.

266
00:22:13,498 --> 00:22:16,084
Oh. Oh, I should just stop talking to you.

267
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:19,254
How can a child be so disrespectful
to her elders?

268
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:20,422
Guess what?

269
00:22:22,424 --> 00:22:24,593
I could be really nasty right now,

270
00:22:24,676 --> 00:22:26,303
but I'm showing you respect.

271
00:22:28,221 --> 00:22:29,973
Because that's what adults do.

272
00:22:40,609 --> 00:22:41,902
Why...

273
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:43,695
The person you are
trying to reach can't answer the phone...

274
00:22:43,779 --> 00:22:46,239
Oh, why aren't you answering the phone?

275
00:22:46,323 --> 00:22:48,200
Always when I need you.

276
00:22:50,911 --> 00:22:52,579
The line you are calling is busy...

277
00:22:52,662 --> 00:22:54,664
MG SAEMAEUL FINANCE FIRM

278
00:22:57,292 --> 00:22:59,419
Yes, I can make
the payments next month.

279
00:23:03,090 --> 00:23:04,716
Right. I apologize.

280
00:23:05,842 --> 00:23:06,760
Yes.

281
00:23:23,819 --> 00:23:26,321
Excuse me, sir. I apologize.

282
00:23:26,905 --> 00:23:29,699
Our department chief says he forgot
that he had a prior engagement...

283
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:31,785
I know you were waiting a while.

284
00:23:32,244 --> 00:23:33,662
I apologize on his behalf.

285
00:23:34,246 --> 00:23:35,414
Could I just see him briefly?

286
00:23:36,706 --> 00:23:38,959
Uh... So he says that he'll call you.

287
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:40,877
He can't see you today.

288
00:23:41,420 --> 00:23:42,629
I apologize.

289
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:49,594
He'd at least need my number then.

290
00:23:50,303 --> 00:23:51,721
Ah, yes, indeed.

291
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:53,557
If you could pass it along...

292
00:23:53,640 --> 00:23:54,724
Yes.

293
00:23:55,684 --> 00:23:57,936
Have a nice day. Goodbye, sir.

294
00:24:03,275 --> 00:24:04,317
Best Fairs?

295
00:24:04,401 --> 00:24:05,527
HAN DONGJIN: CEO, BEST FAIRS

296
00:24:06,736 --> 00:24:10,866
Not only is he ruggedly good-looking,
he's a CEO as well?

297
00:24:11,450 --> 00:24:13,160
So you think he's good-looking?

298
00:24:13,243 --> 00:24:16,121
Hmm. To me, he just seemed like someone
who came here to get a loan.

299
00:24:16,204 --> 00:24:17,581
Listen.

300
00:24:17,664 --> 00:24:20,792
I'm sure you've heard the rumor
that you're a bad judge of men.

301
00:24:20,876 --> 00:24:22,669
They say you're the worst in the branch.

302
00:24:23,253 --> 00:24:24,546
Who's spewing that kind of nonsense?

303
00:24:24,629 --> 00:24:25,797
Me.

304
00:24:26,631 --> 00:24:28,508
It's me.

305
00:24:29,551 --> 00:24:31,052
When I get married next spring,

306
00:24:31,136 --> 00:24:33,388
you're gonna catch my bouquet
when I toss it, right?

307
00:24:33,805 --> 00:24:34,639
Mm-hmm.

308
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:53,241
You've grown up well.

309
00:24:54,951 --> 00:24:56,578
You're the second child, right?

310
00:24:59,456 --> 00:25:02,209
I'm asking you
for the sake of your dead father.

311
00:25:03,210 --> 00:25:05,378
Please can you just remove yourself?

312
00:25:06,296 --> 00:25:08,715
We'll contact you with the burial info.

313
00:25:08,798 --> 00:25:11,384
What's up with the cheap side dishes?

314
00:25:11,468 --> 00:25:13,929
I thought this was a premium suite.

315
00:25:14,012 --> 00:25:15,805
There could be 12

316
00:25:15,889 --> 00:25:17,140
-or nine?
-Hmm?

317
00:25:17,224 --> 00:25:18,808
Eight sides!

318
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:21,144
If not, what about just six, huh?

319
00:25:21,228 --> 00:25:22,395
Or are you too cheap for that?

320
00:25:22,479 --> 00:25:24,773
What? What are you saying, hmm?

321
00:25:29,069 --> 00:25:30,070
What's wrong?

322
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:33,406
You don't like that word?

323
00:25:33,490 --> 00:25:35,200
If you ask me "cheap" suits you.

324
00:25:35,784 --> 00:25:37,661
I guess, everyone here knows that.

325
00:25:37,744 --> 00:25:39,704
Not just cheap but you're...

326
00:25:39,788 --> 00:25:42,874
an overachieving cheap side piece
who stole her friend's husband.

327
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:44,501
-Hey!
-What?

328
00:25:45,168 --> 00:25:46,962
Who are you to raise your voice?

329
00:25:48,838 --> 00:25:50,215
Thirteen years ago,

330
00:25:50,966 --> 00:25:53,134
when the two of you took off
with the bank account book

331
00:25:53,218 --> 00:25:54,094
and the jewelry,

332
00:25:54,177 --> 00:25:55,595
you didn't prepare for this, huh?

333
00:25:57,681 --> 00:25:59,015
Keep your voice down.

334
00:25:59,099 --> 00:26:01,685
What, is this humiliating you?

335
00:26:01,768 --> 00:26:03,770
Your entire life is so embarrassing.

336
00:26:03,853 --> 00:26:05,730
You... you brat!

337
00:26:18,618 --> 00:26:20,370
You just going to stand there?

338
00:26:20,954 --> 00:26:23,456
Hmm, well, I won't leave
until I finish the soju.

339
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:28,003
You didn't really believe
that I'd come here just to humiliate you?

340
00:26:33,508 --> 00:26:36,636
I'm here for the ghost of the man
whose funeral we're attending.

341
00:26:40,056 --> 00:26:42,392
To show him that his daughter
has been waiting for this day

342
00:26:42,475 --> 00:26:43,727
for all these years.

343
00:26:49,274 --> 00:26:50,442
Okay, fine.

344
00:26:50,525 --> 00:26:51,818
You eat up.

345
00:26:53,153 --> 00:26:55,155
Finish eating and then go.

346
00:27:56,549 --> 00:27:57,634
Keep it in.

347
00:27:59,719 --> 00:28:02,222
If you cry right now, you're a loser.

348
00:28:07,936 --> 00:28:11,398
You mean that woman
sold the house in Yeonhui-dong?

349
00:28:11,481 --> 00:28:13,316
Your brother put the deed in her name

350
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:14,734
just before he died.

351
00:28:14,818 --> 00:28:16,903
And then, that ridiculous woman went
and sold it

352
00:28:16,986 --> 00:28:19,239
as soon as her name was on it.

353
00:28:19,322 --> 00:28:20,907
Oh, my gosh. Oh, my gosh.

354
00:28:20,990 --> 00:28:22,450
So then Woojoo came here

355
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:24,828
to confront her
about her house being sold.

356
00:28:24,911 --> 00:28:27,455
I was afraid for the worst,
but it was better than I thought.

357
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:29,874
I was so worried
that she was gonna flip out and...

358
00:28:29,958 --> 00:28:31,710
Oh, I don't know,
throw a table or something.

359
00:28:31,793 --> 00:28:32,669
-Jeez.
-I mean...

360
00:28:32,752 --> 00:28:35,672
That little thing is so fiercely feisty,
you know what I mean?

361
00:28:35,755 --> 00:28:37,132
Goodness.

362
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:38,133
Oh!

363
00:28:39,134 --> 00:28:40,510
Repeat it to me, who sold what?

364
00:28:40,593 --> 00:28:43,680
Oh. Oh, dear. I really have
to use the restroom.

365
00:28:46,349 --> 00:28:48,893
Well, I, uh, so I thought
maybe you'd already left.

366
00:28:48,977 --> 00:28:50,687
-Auntie!
-What, what, huh?

367
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:52,480
Tell me what was sold right now!

368
00:28:53,690 --> 00:28:54,941
Don't look at me like that!

369
00:28:55,024 --> 00:28:56,651
Maybe you should ask Heeja instead of me!

370
00:29:06,870 --> 00:29:08,121
-Let go of me.
-Just come with me.

371
00:29:08,204 --> 00:29:10,665
-Let go and answer me!
-Settle down, let's talk up here.

372
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:11,791
Here...

373
00:29:11,875 --> 00:29:13,001
-Be quiet.
-Just tell me.

374
00:29:13,084 --> 00:29:14,878
Tell me, did you sell our house or not?

375
00:29:14,961 --> 00:29:17,172
I said be quiet and follow me.

376
00:29:17,255 --> 00:29:19,466
Oh, come on! You brat!

377
00:29:19,549 --> 00:29:20,717
I said let go!

378
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:24,804
Why are you doing this to me?

379
00:29:24,888 --> 00:29:27,348
Didn't you crash the funeral
'cause you knew that?

380
00:29:30,018 --> 00:29:31,728
Why the look?

381
00:29:31,811 --> 00:29:34,272
What? Nobody bothered
to mention it to you?

382
00:29:34,355 --> 00:29:36,065
So, you really came here

383
00:29:36,149 --> 00:29:37,984
just to try to punish my dead husband,

384
00:29:38,067 --> 00:29:39,569
looking like a hooker?

385
00:29:41,988 --> 00:29:43,323
Who's really cheap?

386
00:29:43,406 --> 00:29:45,658
Because look who's talking.

387
00:29:45,742 --> 00:29:47,368
Explain it then.

388
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:49,162
Tell me, why would it belong to you?

389
00:29:49,245 --> 00:29:50,789
Because it doesn't, okay?

390
00:29:50,872 --> 00:29:52,123
Hang on a sec.

391
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:54,083
You should do something about your phone.

392
00:29:54,167 --> 00:29:56,503
It's driving me crazy.

393
00:29:59,923 --> 00:30:01,257
-Look, I'll call you later--
-Woojoo!

394
00:30:01,341 --> 00:30:03,718
Why don't you answer your phone?

395
00:30:03,802 --> 00:30:05,845
Some people are here
telling me to vacate the house...

396
00:30:08,598 --> 00:30:10,350
We'll need to change it all out.

397
00:30:10,433 --> 00:30:11,810
Right? New wallpaper?

398
00:30:13,812 --> 00:30:15,647
Please, Woojoo, where are you?

399
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:16,773
The house is mine!

400
00:30:16,856 --> 00:30:18,316
Keep your voice down!

401
00:30:18,399 --> 00:30:20,944
What makes you think it's okay
to shout at me like that?

402
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:25,114
Look, your father and I
were legally married you get it?

403
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:28,034
That house was under your father's name.

404
00:30:28,117 --> 00:30:30,203
It belonged to you then,
but now it's an inheritance.

405
00:30:30,286 --> 00:30:31,538
It was mine to sell.

406
00:30:31,621 --> 00:30:34,040
-I haven't done anything wrong, okay?
-Well, you can't just force us out.

407
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:36,709
You can't just take away our home,
we live there still.

408
00:30:37,752 --> 00:30:38,753
I swear...

409
00:30:38,837 --> 00:30:41,297
If you take our home away from us,
karma will come for you.

410
00:30:41,381 --> 00:30:43,091
You can't uproot us like that,
how could you?

411
00:30:44,634 --> 00:30:46,302
You really think karma exists?

412
00:30:46,386 --> 00:30:48,805
I'll consider the humiliation
I endured today

413
00:30:48,888 --> 00:30:50,223
as punishment enough.

414
00:30:50,306 --> 00:30:51,558
About the house?

415
00:30:51,641 --> 00:30:53,351
You have a week to move out.

416
00:30:56,563 --> 00:30:57,730
Take this.

417
00:30:58,439 --> 00:30:59,732
Use it to catch a cab.

418
00:31:00,733 --> 00:31:02,944
You can't go on the bus looking like that.

419
00:31:04,362 --> 00:31:06,739
Where are you going?
We're not finished yet.

420
00:31:06,823 --> 00:31:07,907
What the hell?

421
00:31:08,533 --> 00:31:10,285
Don't you touch me!

422
00:31:10,368 --> 00:31:11,911
I'm done being nice,

423
00:31:11,995 --> 00:31:14,497
you need to respect me
and your dead father.

424
00:31:14,581 --> 00:31:17,876
Stop this now unless you want you
and your precious siblings...

425
00:31:17,959 --> 00:31:20,336
...pulled out by force.

426
00:31:35,518 --> 00:31:36,978
Oh!

427
00:31:38,438 --> 00:31:39,772
Whoo!

428
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:45,528
Shoot.

429
00:31:51,534 --> 00:31:53,244
Mmm.

430
00:31:53,328 --> 00:31:54,287
Hmm?

431
00:31:55,830 --> 00:31:57,832
DONGJIN:
123 HAMCHON-RO, DONGJAK-GU, SEOUL

432
00:31:57,916 --> 00:31:59,000
Ah, eeesh!

433
00:32:03,755 --> 00:32:04,672
Hey...

434
00:32:18,603 --> 00:32:19,729
Hey, where did you get the car key?

435
00:32:19,812 --> 00:32:21,689
Where do you think I got it?

436
00:32:25,735 --> 00:32:27,487
I guess you went through my desk.

437
00:32:27,570 --> 00:32:28,821
Anyway.

438
00:32:29,614 --> 00:32:31,157
This is kidnapping, you know?

439
00:32:31,240 --> 00:32:33,701
Do you know how scared
my baby must have been?

440
00:32:33,785 --> 00:32:34,869
When did you get the car?

441
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:38,623
Like...

442
00:32:39,582 --> 00:32:42,085
a while... ago, I think.

443
00:32:42,168 --> 00:32:44,170
I paid for it a little before that.

444
00:32:44,754 --> 00:32:47,507
It was before things got so bad.

445
00:32:51,761 --> 00:32:53,096
Say something okay?

446
00:32:53,179 --> 00:32:55,139
Dongjin, don't just give me that look.

447
00:32:55,682 --> 00:32:57,100
As co-owner...

448
00:32:57,183 --> 00:32:59,936
I'm also working hard
to find some cash flow for us.

449
00:33:00,019 --> 00:33:02,021
So please don't make me sell my car!

450
00:33:02,105 --> 00:33:03,731
You find some money, okay?

451
00:33:05,191 --> 00:33:06,317
I will do what I can.

452
00:33:07,026 --> 00:33:08,945
Hey, did things go well at the bank?

453
00:33:09,028 --> 00:33:10,405
How much are they gonna loan us?

454
00:33:10,488 --> 00:33:11,781
Hey, Dongjin!

455
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:15,243
Hey! Can you please just tell me
what's gonna happen with the company?

456
00:33:24,252 --> 00:33:26,838
JEIL FUNERAL PARLOR

457
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:33,678
Dongjin, you actually came here?

458
00:33:35,471 --> 00:33:37,598
Nothing good's gonna come outta this.

459
00:34:04,709 --> 00:34:05,835
Chulmin.

460
00:34:06,544 --> 00:34:08,421
Dongjin is here to see you.

461
00:34:11,674 --> 00:34:13,634
You didn't see him often.

462
00:34:13,718 --> 00:34:15,094
Mm.

463
00:34:15,178 --> 00:34:16,179
But...

464
00:34:16,804 --> 00:34:18,848
he was always good to you.

465
00:34:18,931 --> 00:34:20,683
You remember, right?

466
00:34:21,851 --> 00:34:25,104
You left the world first,
leaving me all alone.

467
00:34:25,688 --> 00:34:28,524
Now, this boy is all I have left.

468
00:34:32,153 --> 00:34:34,405
Why did you have to go so early?

469
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:39,410
Tell me why you left me all by myself.

470
00:35:46,394 --> 00:35:48,688
Ah, stop it already, it's stupid.

471
00:36:25,349 --> 00:36:27,310
Ah, Woojoo, did you do something crazy?

472
00:36:28,352 --> 00:36:30,938
I was hoping I wouldn't find you
when I got here.

473
00:36:31,022 --> 00:36:33,024
But my hunch was right...

474
00:36:33,107 --> 00:36:35,193
I wish I had been wrong.

475
00:36:35,902 --> 00:36:38,362
Like what impulsive decision convinced you

476
00:36:38,446 --> 00:36:40,364
that it'd be okay
to dress like that at a funeral?

477
00:36:42,450 --> 00:36:43,659
Come on. Why don't you get up?

478
00:36:57,048 --> 00:36:59,425
Are you... crying?

479
00:37:09,101 --> 00:37:10,311
Hey, please don't cry.

480
00:37:14,815 --> 00:37:16,108
Go ahead and say it.

481
00:37:17,443 --> 00:37:19,111
"Woojoo, why do you even come?"

482
00:37:21,197 --> 00:37:24,825
I tried so hard to hold myself together
so my dad wouldn't see these tears.

483
00:37:26,202 --> 00:37:28,537
And now if they see me here...

484
00:37:29,121 --> 00:37:32,375
they'll think that I'm broken
'cause of his death and that's not why.

485
00:37:33,251 --> 00:37:35,878
I didn't want to cry for him at all.

486
00:38:14,709 --> 00:38:15,793
You're cruel, you know.

487
00:38:16,544 --> 00:38:18,754
You don't visit me once for five years,

488
00:38:18,838 --> 00:38:22,258
and it takes someone to die
just for me to see your face?

489
00:38:37,648 --> 00:38:39,233
I transferred the money.

490
00:38:39,317 --> 00:38:40,818
You should check your bank.

491
00:38:43,487 --> 00:38:44,655
I'm sorry.

492
00:38:47,116 --> 00:38:49,410
I know I got married a lot

493
00:38:50,036 --> 00:38:52,788
so I guess I didn't offer you
the support you needed.

494
00:38:53,122 --> 00:38:56,959
Though I endured,
much anxiety and pain during your birth.

495
00:38:57,043 --> 00:39:00,379
If you were having a hard time,
you should have talked to me sooner.

496
00:39:00,463 --> 00:39:03,716
Why would you be running around
and asking everyone for money like a bum?

497
00:39:10,473 --> 00:39:12,266
Where did you get the money though?

498
00:39:14,685 --> 00:39:16,354
It wasn't stolen.

499
00:39:16,437 --> 00:39:17,521
Just so we're clear.

500
00:39:20,232 --> 00:39:21,484
I'll pay you back.

501
00:39:25,821 --> 00:39:27,823
There were so many people looking.

502
00:39:27,907 --> 00:39:30,034
You should have at least gotten a haircut.

503
00:39:38,542 --> 00:39:39,585
Okay.

504
00:39:40,753 --> 00:39:42,797
Now you're acting like your dad's son.

505
00:39:49,678 --> 00:39:50,930
Oh, Dongjin.

506
00:39:51,013 --> 00:39:54,141
Let's see each other more often, okay?

507
00:39:56,894 --> 00:40:01,023
You know, I have no one but you now.

508
00:40:01,524 --> 00:40:03,943
That's all. Hm?

509
00:40:42,773 --> 00:40:45,818
Hey, before we go,
do you wanna get takeout from our area?

510
00:40:45,901 --> 00:40:48,279
What if the jjajangmyeon
in the new neighborhood sucks?

511
00:40:48,362 --> 00:40:50,698
Yeah, I wouldn't like that at all.

512
00:40:52,658 --> 00:40:54,618
Do you wanna get kang jjajangmyeon
in that case?

513
00:40:54,702 --> 00:40:56,078
Yeah, sure, the seafood one.

514
00:40:57,371 --> 00:40:59,999
Oh, in that case,
I'll get some fried rice.

515
00:41:00,082 --> 00:41:01,709
You want sweet and sour pork?

516
00:41:01,792 --> 00:41:02,793
Sweet and sour?

517
00:41:02,877 --> 00:41:04,712
Huh, let's get a medium size.

518
00:41:09,091 --> 00:41:10,968
Hi, this is the house
with the ginkgo tree out front.

519
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:14,263
I'd like two seafood jjajangmyeon,
a fried rice,

